  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthen the fundaments of CDFA: financial management governance and business</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A financially self-sustaining organisation, able to cover its core costs in 2018 from membership fees; provide quality services to 5,000 members generated through agribusiness, focusing on improved crop production and productivity, improved marketing and a running a profitable agribusiness.
Chadiza District Farmers Association (CDFA) was established in 1998 and the Association was officially registered on 9th May, 2005 with the Registrar of Societies under the laws of Zambia. The reason to establish CDFA was to improve food and income security amongst its members by providing services with an educational and business component. The number of members in 2017 is 608. Membership fluctuates largely from year to year. CDFA members are small to medium-sized emerging farmers that are gradually producing for the market.

Through effective service provision using lead farmers this BHAG will be achieved. Support is needed in governance, financial management, services provision and business development. As another donor supports the agribusiness component, Agriterra will not intervene in this implementation but will support in the marekting aspects.

A financially self-sustaining organisation, able to cover its core costs in 2018 from membership fees; provide quality services to 5,000 members generated through agribusiness, focusing on improved crop production and productivity, improved marketing and a running a profitable agribusiness.</narrative>
  </description>
